org.apache.derbyTesting.junit

Class JDBCDataSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.derbyTesting.junit.JDBCDataSource

  • public class JDBCDataSource
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility methods related to JDBC DataSource objects. J2EEDataSource exists to return XA and connection pooling data sources.
    See Also:
    J2EEDataSource

      • getDataSourceObject

        static javax.sql.DataSource getDataSourceObject(java.lang.String classname,
                                                java.util.HashMap beanProperties)
        Return a DataSource object of the passed in type configured with the passed in Java bean properties. This will actually work with any object that has Java bean setter methods.
        If a thread context class loader exists then it is used to try and load the class.
